tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function shows mildly elevated serum creatinine, suggesting possible early renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals glucosuria, ketonuria, bilirubinuria, low specific gravity, and proteinuria, with abnormal urine appearance and color, but no evidence of infection. Hemoglobin A1c is unexpectedly low, which may indicate analytical error or a condition affecting red cell turnover. Findings suggest possible renal dysfunction and metabolic derangement; correlation with clinical context and further evaluation are recommended.
